==English==

===Noun===

'''Tory'''

#(''Historical'') A member of the British political party or faction from which the Conservative Party was later created, aiming to uphold the rights of the monarchy and the privileges of the established Church (the Church of England).
#A member or supporter of the British Conservative Party or of the Canadian Progressive Conservative Party.
#(''Historical'') An opponent of independence at the time of the American Revolution.

===Adjective===

#Of or belonging to the Tory Party or the Conservative Party.